column1: # Title: Deetman et al. (2021) share of underground lines for high, medium, and low voltage lines by IMAGE3.0 regions

# Description: Deetman et al. used an empirical relationship to calculate percent share of high, medium, and low voltage lines underground (vs. overhead), as a function of per capita GDP. For high voltage, the relationship is pct_underground_HV = 0.0009*PCgdp - 15.102. For medium voltage, the relationship is pct_underground_MV = 0.0016*PCgdp - 4.769. For low voltage, the relationship is pct_underground_LV = 0.0016 + 7.5104.
# Source: Deetman et al. 2021 Resources, Conservation and Recycling https://doi.org/10.1016/j.resconrec.2020.105200

column2: Per capita income in 2016 (in 2005 US$/capita, PPP)
